<GUIClass name="CMUI_PointDrawingFrame" id="2cdb6f95-26a9-44f4-a1da-f4c23ba4bf9a">
    <superclass name="CMUI_DrawingFrame"/>
    <transient/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <DbClassMap file="_usergui"/>
    <Constant name="Mode_DisplayOnly" id="655b765e-c981-4c03-b3e9-b92682715f3b">
        <source>3</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>This mode is used during the display version of the overview.

It allows us to view terminal area polygons.

In this mode you can not draw lines, move polygons, rotate polygons or resize polygons in anyway.</text>
    </Constant>
    <Constant name="Mode_LineAlter" id="fe87cfae-39b9-4723-85ab-033d02cbb025">
        <source>2</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>This mode is only used during the edit.

It allows us to grab any point in a polygon and pull that point to a new position.

This allows us to draw any shape with as many side as we like.

In this mode you can not rotate polygons or draw lines.</text>
    </Constant>
    <Constant name="Mode_LineDrawing" id="a4119228-30b3-470b-92a0-ca2d6af44c33">
        <source>1</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>This mode is only used during the edit of the TERMINAL, not the terminal areas.

It allows us to draw lines that are joined together until we click on the first point of the polygon.
At that point the polygon is complete.

This allows us to draw any shape with as many side as we like.

In this mode you can not rotate polygons or resize any polygon in anyway.

When the polygon is complete and saved it can be manipulated.</text>
    </Constant>
    <Constant name="Mode_LinePullLR" id="54337595-ea0c-4edc-94f4-847123b2cfe5">
        <source>5</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
    </Constant>
    <Constant name="Mode_LinePullUD" id="5b309935-30e8-4dd6-8c9d-3c70c9580b6b">
        <source>6</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
    </Constant>
    <Constant name="Mode_MultiSelect" id="832ce11c-decf-4358-91f0-96618942b036">
        <source>8</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
    </Constant>
    <Constant name="Mode_PolyMove" id="dd1a57cb-81d2-4285-b867-ef0d572ddb3f">
        <source>4</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>This mode is used during the edit version of the overview.

It allows us to move the whole of the current polygon.

In this mode you can not draw lines, rotate polygons or resize polygons by grabbing any point.</text>
    </Constant>
    <Constant name="Mode_Work" id="812a8b1c-9da5-48f0-af10-e77eac2980c3">
        <source>9</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
    </Constant>
